ung von Differenz im Kontext machtpolitischer Auseinandersetzungen und deren unterschiedlich erfahrene Wirklichkeiten.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aAmerika. 4aAmerikanische Geschichte. 4aGeschichtswissenschaft. 4aKolonialgeschichte. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aPostkoloniale Theorie. 4aPostkolonialismus. 4aRepräsentation. 4aSymbol. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aAmerican History.  aCultural History.  aHistory of Colonialism.  aHistory.  aPostcolonialism.1 aBahrs, Karoline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBahrs, Karoline, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBaumbach, Kora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerrenberg, Jeanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBessler, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlumtritt, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBock, Ulrike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrust, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCostas, Gundo Rial Y, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDa Silva, Inga Scharf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDöhl, Frédéric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEbert, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEbert, Anne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGolte, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGomez, Pablo F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoltz, Menja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relator